</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Son.</SPEAKER>
<P>Nothing can be plainer, I think.</P>
</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Fa.</SPEAKER>
<P><HI>Here</HI> is our Saviour in the Glory of the Di|vine
Nature, and <HI>There</HI> again in the lowe&s;t State
of his Incarnation; <HI>Here</HI> as <HI>Jehovah, There</HI> as the
Mediator; <HI>Here</HI> as the Lord our Maker, <HI>There</HI> as
the Lord our Saviour; <HI>Here as</HI> GOD over all,
ble&s;&s;ed for ever, <HI>There</HI> as lifted up, and drawing all
Men to him; <HI>Here</HI> in the Form of GOD, <HI>There</HI> in
the Form of a Servant; <HI>Here</HI> he is the Image of the
invi&s;ible God, the expre&s;s Image; the Word, which
was in the Beginning, and which was with God,
and was GOD, really GOD; <HI>There</HI> the Son of Man,
and really Man, or the Deity or Humanity toge|ther,
