</SP>
<SP>
<SPEAKER>Fa.</SPEAKER>
<P>But now di&s;tingui&s;hing rightly of the two
Natures in Chri&s;t, and &s;peaking of him, or un|der&s;tanding
him to &s;peak of him&s;elf, in the di|&s;tinct
Capacities of a GOD incarnated, and of a Man,
it is &s;till plainer; &s;peaking of him as real GOD, <HI>the
Creator of the World, by whom all Things were made,</HI>
